## Why This Is Asked
Assesses ability to design comprehensive performance tests for multi-stage pipelines under bursty traffic, focusing on latency distribution, autoscaling behavior, backpressure mechanisms, and failure prevention strategies.

## Key Concepts
- End-to-end latency measurement with p50/p95/p99 percentiles
- Bounded queues and backpressure for flow control
- Circuit breakers and fail-fast paths for failure isolation
- Autoscaling responsiveness and resource constraint management
- Distributed tracing for per-stage telemetry and bottleneck identification

## Code Example
```java
// Load profile configuration
public class LoadProfile {
    private final int baseThroughput;
    private final int burstMultiplier;
    private final Duration burstDuration;
    private final List<FrameSize> frameSizes;

    public static LoadProfile videoProcessingTest() {
        return new LoadProfile(1000, 5, Duration.ofMinutes(20),
            Arrays.asList(FrameSize.SMALL, FrameSize.MEDIUM, FrameSize.LARGE));
    }
}

// Performance test implementation
public class PipelinePerformanceTest {

    @Test
    public void testEndToEndLatency() {
        LoadProfile profile = LoadProfile.videoProcessingTest();
        MetricsCollector collector = new MetricsCollector();

        // Generate bursty traffic
        CompletableFuture<Void> test = CompletableFuture.runAsync(() -> {
            generateTraffic(profile, collector);
        });

        // Monitor autoscaler responsiveness
        monitorAutoscaling(collector);

        // Validate SLA adherence
        test.thenRun(() -> validateSLAs(collector));
    }

    private void validateSLAs(MetricsCollector collector) {
        LatencyMetrics latency = collector.getLatencyMetrics();
        assertTrue(latency.getP95() < Duration.ofSeconds(10));
        assertTrue(latency.getP99() < Duration.ofSeconds(15));

        AutoscalingMetrics autoscaling = collector.getAutoscalingMetrics();
        assertTrue(autoscaling.getScaleUpTime() < Duration.ofMinutes(2));
    }
}
```

